ISLAMABAD, Jan 12 (APP): Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif Thursday thanked the European Union for its commitment of $ 97 million for Pakistan’s flood affectees.
In a tweet on social media platform Twitter, he said, “Thank you to the European Union for its commitment of $97 million for Pakistan’s flood-affectees. The multifaceted relations between Pakistan & EU have grown over the decades.”“The European Union continues to remain one of Pakistan’s largest trading & development partners & export destination,” he added.
